<HL>
   Technology:
   Upjohn Reaches Marketing Pact
</HL>
<DATE>
09/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   UPJ
</CO>
<IN>
DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)
</IN>
<LP>
   KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Upjohn Co. said it agreed to
co-promote its dermatology products with Owen/Galderma
Laboratories Inc., a marketer of dermatological products.
   An Upjohn official said Owen/Galderma will contribute 57
sales representatives to expand the pharmaceutical concern's
sales force in promoting Rogaine Topical Solution
male-pattern baldness drug and Cleocin T acne product line to
dermatologists in the U.S.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   "We feel this focus on dermatologists will help with the
continued growth of Celocin T and Rogaine," Upjohn said. The
agreement is effective Jan. 1.
</TEXT>
